<http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlab105>
    bibo:endPage "1286" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2022-02-07" ;
    bibo:startPage "1245" ;
    bibo:volume "195" ;
    dc:creator "Sites, Robert W." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Phylogeny and revised classification of the saucer bugs (Hemiptera: Nepomorpha: Naucoridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994631>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994635>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994654>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994658>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994629>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994656> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994631>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Habitus examples of each subfamily: Ambrysinae: Ambrysus signoreti (a), Cheirochelinae: Cheirochela thailandana (b), Cryphocricinae: Cryphocricos hungerfordi (c), Ilyocorinae: Ilyocoris cimicoides (d), Laccocorinae: Laccocoris limicola (e), Limnocorinae: Limnocoris inornatus (f), Macrocorinae subfam. nov.: Macrocoris flavicollis (g), Naucorinae: Naucoris scutellaris (Thailand) (h)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994631/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994635>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Examples of male genital capsule with pygophore, aedeagus and parameres (terga IX and X removed) for each subfamily: Ambrysinae: Ambrysus lunatus (a), Cheirochelinae: Coptocatus kinabalu (b), Cryphocricinae: Cryphocricos hungerfordi (c), Ilyocorinae:Ilyocoris cimicoides (d), Laccocorinae: Laccocoris spurcus (e), Limnocorinae: Limnocoris ovatulus (f), Macrocorinae subfam. nov.: Macrocoris flavicollis (g), Naucorinae: Afronaucoris gen. nov.: Afronaucoris madagascariensis (h)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994654>
    dc:description "Figure 17. Lateral view of head and prothorax of Philippinocoris usingeri showing anteromedian tooth of prosternum (white arrow)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994658>
    dc:description "Figure 19. Revised generic representation of the former genus Naucoris. Dorsal habitus of Naucoris maculatus (a), Australonaucoris congrex (b), Afronaucoris parvulus (c), Indonaucoris minutus sp. nov. (d)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994658/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994629>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Most Probable Phylogeny dendogram based on Bayesian inference with substitutions from maximum likelihood for Laccocorinae (except Ctenipocorini trib. nov. and Idiocarini trib. nov.). Closer views of Laccocorinae and Naucorinae individually can be seen in Figures 13 and 18, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994629/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994656>
    dc:description "Figure 18. Detail of Most Probable Phylogeny dendogram of Naucorinae, based primarily on Bayesian inference, but with maximum likelihood topology substituted for Idiocarini trib. nov. All species of Afronaucoris gen. nov. and Australonaucoris gen. nov. are new combinations. The red box in the inset shows the part of Figure 9 depicted in this figure." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994656/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

